  "text": "The Kafka producer timeout error 'Expiring N record(s) for topic-partition' originates from three key components: (1) The TimeoutException class (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/TimeoutException.java) defines the exception type thrown when batches expire. (2) The record batch expiration logic is implemented in two files: Sender.java's sendProducerData() method (lines 415-418) constructs the error message and instantiates the TimeoutException, while RecordAccumulator.java's expiredBatches() method (lines 465-486) identifies and returns batches that have exceeded the delivery timeout. The expiration check uses batch.hasReachedDeliveryTimeout(deliveryTimeoutMs, now) to determine if a batch should expire. (3) The delivery.timeout.ms configuration constant is defined in ProducerConfig.java (line 165) as DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG and controls the upper bound time for reporting success or failure after send() returns. The error chain flows: sendProducerData() calls accumulator.expiredBatches(now), which evaluates each batch against the deliveryTimeoutMs limit, returning those that have expired. For each expired batch, sendProducerData() constructs an error message including the record count and elapsed time, then creates a TimeoutException with this message and calls failBatch() to handle the failure."
}

